This paper deals with word embeddings, which are a popular technique in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a method for creating interpretable and domain-informed dimensions for word embeddings, which involves the use of informative priors. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which all deal with methods for processing and analyzing large amounts of data. Finally, the paper's focus on computational social science and digital humanities suggests that it could also be relevant to the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
